  "prompt": "What is regression?",
  "response": "Regression is a statistical method used to analyze the relationship between one or more independent variables (predictors) and a dependent variable (target). It helps in understanding how the dependent variable changes when the independent variables are modified. Here are key points about regression:\n\n1. Types of Regression:\n- Linear Regression\n- Logistic Regression\n- Polynomial Regression\n- Multiple Regression\n- Ridge Regression\n- Lasso Regression\n\n2. Main Purposes:\n- Predicting numeric outcomes\n- Understanding variable relationships\n- Identifying important predictors\n- Estimating trends and patterns\n\n3. Linear Regression Characteristics:\n- Assumes linear relationship between variables\n- Finds best-fit line minimizing prediction errors\n- Uses least squares method\n- Produces a mathematical equation\n\n4. Key Metrics:\n- R-squared value\n- Mean Squared Error\n- Coefficients\n- P-values\n\n5. Applications:\n- Sales forecasting\n- Economic modeling\n- Risk assessment\n- Machine learning\n- Scientific research\n- Healthcare predictions\n\n6. Assumptions:\n- Linear relationship\n- Independent observations\n- Normally distributed residuals\n- Homoscedasticity\n- No multicollinearity\n\nRegression helps transform complex data relationships into understandable, predictive models.",
